parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "GROMACS",
"software": [
"GROMACS 2020.3",
"OpenMPI 1.10.2",
"CUDA Toolkit 10.2.89",
"GCC 9.3.0"
],
"resource_requirements": [
"1 node",
"1 processor per node",
"240 hours walltime"
]
}
```

The script uses **GROMACS** to perform a molecular dynamics simulation. It loads necessary modules for **CUDA Toolkit**, **OpenMPI**, and **GCC**. It allocates **1 node** with **1 processor** and sets a **240 hours walltime** limit. The script defines the number of processors and loads necessary modules before running the **gmx grompp** command. The **gmx grompp** command is used to generate a simulation input file (tpr) from a topology file (top), a configuration file (gro), and a simulation parameter file (mdp).
